Generated the Animated ImageView developer guide at `docs/generated/animated-image-view.md`. The document covers:

- Creating and configuring `AnimatedImageView` instances
- Loading animated images (single files and URL frame sequences)
- Playback control (`Play()`, `Pause()`, `Stop()`, `JumpToFrame()`)
- Animation settings (loop count, speed factor, frame delay, stop behavior)
- Alpha masking with crop-to-mask and masking mode options
- Loading and caching policies (load policy, release policy, synchronous loading)
- Signals for animation completion and resource readiness
- Image appearance settings (fitting mode, sampling mode, desired size, tinting, pixel area)

All code examples use the `Dali::Ui::AnimatedImageView` API surface and are grounded in the sample files from the repository.
